# Repository Scripts Directory

This section provides a detailed mapping of the SQL script files available within each repository, linking them directly to our data analytics roadmap.

---

## 📁 Repository 1: Exploratory SQL Analysis
*Source files extracted from image_6e44bd.png*

This repository contains the foundational scripts used to discover, clean, and profile the dataset before running complex business logic.

*   **`Data_Base_Exploration.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Handles schema discovery, table relationships audit, and total row count evaluations across the database.
*   **`Dimension Exploration.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Profiles categorical columns to check for distinct values, cardinality, and missing text entries.
*   **`Date Exploration.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Sets the time-horizon boundaries by extracting the minimum/maximum dates and identifying timeline gaps.
*   **`Measure Exploration.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Executes high-level aggregations (`SUM`, `AVG`, `COUNT`) to establish the initial baseline business metrics.
*   **`Magnitude Analysis.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Measures the spread, scale, and variances of numerical inputs to flag outliers or anomalies.
*   **`Ranking Analysis.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Leverages window ranking functions to isolate top-performing and underperforming records (Top N / Bottom N analysis).

---

## 📁 Repository 2: Advanced SQL Analytics
*Source files extracted from image_6e44b8.png*

This repository features advanced query patterns, mathematical formulations, and final views structured for stakeholder reporting and BI integration.

*   **`Change over time.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Employs time-series analytical functions (`LAG`/`LEAD`) to calculate period-over-period growth rates.
*   **`Cumulative Analysis.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Calculates running totals and rolling averages to observe long-term data accumulation patterns.
*   **`Performance Analysis.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Runs variance assessments against benchmarks, targets, or past performance milestones.
*   **`Part to whole analysis.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Determines proportional contributions using partition-based division to get exact percentage-of-total values.
*   **`Data Segmentation.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* Implements conditional classification logic (`CASE WHEN`) to build customer cohorts or behavioral groupings.
*   **`Customer_report.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* A compiled operational script designed to deliver comprehensive insights specifically focused on customer metrics and behavior.
*   **`Product_report.sql`**
    *   *Purpose:* A consolidated reporting query structured to track product line performance, category share, and moving item trends.
